{[%evp 0,31,24,22,22,22,22,30,39,39,39,32,38,29,27,19,22,27,47,45,42,42,56,42,
61,51,55,54,54,44,35,44,17,31]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 (2. Bf4 e6 3. Nf3 {This will
be our move-order}) 2... e6 3. Bf4 b6 {This move will be the usual choice of
NID/QID players. Black can also start with ...c7-c5. The advance ...c7-c5,
however, does not have independent value since later on Black will either play
