} 5. Bg5 Be7 6. Ne5 {when the h5-knight is vulnerable. Black has no equality
here.} Nf6 ({The alternative is} 6... Bxg5 7. Qxh5 O-O (7... g6 $4 8. Qf3 $18 {
[%cal Gf3f7,Gf3a8]}) 8. Bd3 g6 9. Qf3 {[%cal Gh2h4,Gh4h5] White's idea was to
provoke ...g7-g6. Now, the g6-pawn can be used as a hook. White is going to
