provoke kingside weaknesses.} f5 11. Nxd7 Nxd7 12. a4 {[%csl Ra5,Rb6,Rc5] I
like this idea. White immediately fixes Black's queenside weaknesses. A
possible continuation would be} Ba6 13. Bxa6 Rxa6 14. Qe2 Ra8 15. c4 $1 $14 {
Played in accordance with the classical principles. When there are multiple
