{[%evp 0,67,24,15,31,19,51,40,40,40,35,-7,-5,-2,-2,-2,22,24,29,16,11,32,28,-4,
6,-1,-1,2,2,10,8,8,23,13,47,34,63,63,63,54,61,54,38,77,52,36,43,29,27,66,83,83,
165,172,163,156,187,156,165,146,178,198,226,226,183,154,192,183,192,216]} 1. d4
Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Bf4 {Levon stucks to the line which put him through
against Maxime in the World Cup.} Bg7 5. Nb5 Na6 6. e3 c6 7. Nc3 O-O $6 8. Bxa6
$14 bxa6 9. h3 {I don't think White needs h3 anymore but in a blitz game it's
always good to have your pawn on h3 rather than h2.} Nd7 10. O-O Bb7 11. Na4
Rc8 $6 (11... c5 {This has to be played, after} 12. c3 {Black is still
slightly worse but he is still in there.}) 12. b4 $1 a5 13. Nc5 Nxc5 14. bxc5 {
A dream position for White especially in a blitz game.} Ba6 15. Re1 a4 16. Qd2
Bb5 17. e4 $1 dxe4 18. Rxe4 Bc4 19. Bh6 $2 (19. Re3 Bd5 20. Ne5 $16) 19... Bxh6
$2 (19... Bd5 20. Bxg7 Kxg7 21. Re3 (21. Rh4 h5 22. Rxh5 gxh5 23. Qg5+ {
is only a perpetual}) 21... Bxf3 22. Rxf3 Qd5 {and all of a sudden Black has
serious chances to hold.}) 20. Qxh6 f6 21. Nd2 Bd5 22. Re3 Rb8 23. c4 Bf7 24.
Re4 g5 25. Rae1 e5 (25... Rb7 {Black can still try and resist but the odds of
him holding on against Aronian are close to zero,} 26. h4) 26. dxe5 Bg6 (26...
Qxd2 27. exf6 {with mate in 4?}) 27. R4e2 {he only thing left for Levon now is
not to lose on time.} Rb2 28. Nf3 Rxe2 29. Rxe2 fxe5 30. Rxe5 Qd1+ 31. Re1 Qc2
32. a3 Qxc4 33. Qxg5 Rf5 34. Re8+ Kg7 35. Qe7+ Kh6 36. Qe3+ Qf4 37. Qxf4+ Rxf4
38. Re6 Rc4 39. Rxc6 Kg7 40. Ne5 Rc1+ 41. Kh2 Be4 42. Ra6 Rxc5 43. Rxa7+ Kg8
44. Nd7 Rf5 45. Rxa4 Bc6 46. Rg4+ Kf7 47. Nb8 Bb7 48. f3 Rb5 49. Rb4 Rxb4 50.
axb4 {After such a terrible start in the event Levon crawled his way back to
win the tournament which shows what a true champion he is!} 1-0

