{[%evp 0,71,31,18,29,27,27,21,20,14,32,22,29,19,14,-6,8,7,11,25,19,-6,-14,-80,
-79,-79,-93,-91,-96,-85,-90,-47,-59,-53,-4,-59,-62,-65,-45,-64,-79,-61,-20,1,
-4,-3,10,0,9,321,111,52,96,97,97,97,65,83,90,87,86,100,181,228,315,391,873,889,
890,943,949,928,1184,1392]} {This is a perfect attacking game in the old main
line. Jorden van Foreest won without making any mistakes.} 1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6
3. e3 e6 4. Nd2 c5 5. Ngf3 Nc6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Bg3 O-O 8. Bd3 b6 9. e4 Be7 10. e5
Nh5 11. Ng5 Bxg5 12. Qxh5 g6 13. Qe2 cxd4 14. h4 {All this until here has been
covered in the theoretical chapter.} Bxd2+ 15. Qxd2 dxc3 16. bxc3 {Without his
dark-squared bishop on the board, Black can hardly defend here.} d4 17. c4 Qe7
18. Rb1 {An important prophylactic move. White prevents the exchange of the
queens via the b4-square.} h5 19. Bf4 {[%cal Gf4g5,Gg5f6] The bishop is now
heading to the f6-square.} Bb7 20. O-O Rfc8 21. Bg5 Qf8 22. Bf6 Ne7 23. Qg5 {
White's attack is already decisive. White converted his advantage without the
slightest trouble.} Nf5 24. Bxf5 exf5 25. e6 Kh7 26. e7 Qe8 27. Rfd1 Rxc4 28.
Rxd4 Rxd4 29. Bxd4 Qc6 30. Rd1 Qd6 31. Rd2 Re8 32. Be3 Qxe7 33. Qh6+ Kg8 34.
Bd4 f6 35. Qxg6+ Kf8 36. Bxf6 1-0

