{[%evp 0,59,38,15,20,20,18,18,42,44,35,27,26,27,26,18,18,9,10,10,5,5,19,-2,42,
12,11,0,0,6,7,4,14,-36,-45,-82,5,0,-29,-110,47,47,128,128,115,128,113,119,112,
112,109,109,155,127,161,144,154,169,167,167,167,175]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3.
Bf4 b6 4. e3 Bb7 5. h3 Be7 6. Bd3 O-O 7. O-O c5 8. c3 Nc6 9. Nbd2 d5 10. Qe2
Bd6 11. Rfe1 {A typical waiting from Magnus!} Ne7 12. Rad1 {Another calm,
improving move and a good one, as will become clear over the next few moves.}
Ng6 13. Bxg6 $1 hxg6 14. Bxd6 Qxd6 15. Ne5 {The point of White's play becomes
clear. Black has been saddled with a bad bishop and finds himself a touch
worse.} g5 $6 {This is simply bad now} 16. f4 $1 gxf4 17. Rf1 $1 {The
refutation,not an easy move to see from far} Nd7 (17... fxe3 18. Rxf6 $1 exd2 (
18... gxf6 $2 19. Qg4+ Kh8 20. Rf1 $1 exd2 21. Rf4 {leads to a forced mate})
19. Rxd2 Qe7 (19... gxf6 20. Qg4+ Kh8 21. Rd3) 20. Ng4 $1 {[%cal Ge2e5]} cxd4
21. Nh6+ gxh6 22. Qg4+ Kh7 23. Rdf2 $18 {[%csl Gh6][%cal Gg4h5]}) 18. Qh5 {
Another top move by Carlsen} Nf6 (18... fxe3 $2 19. Nxf7 {,}) (18... cxd4 19.
exd4 Nxe5 20. dxe5 Qc5+ 21. Rf2 Ba6 22. Re1 Bd3 23. Nb3 Qe7 24. Rxf4 $40) 19.
Qh4 Qd8 (19... fxe3 20. Rxf6 $1 {The same idea works here as well.}) 20. Rxf4
Ne4 (20... cxd4 21. exd4 Ne4 22. Qe1 $40) 21. Nxe4 Qxh4 (21... dxe4 22. Qh5 $18
{[%cal Gf4h4] .}) 22. Rxh4 dxe4 23. dxc5 {Now White is simply winning this
endgame} bxc5 24. Rd7 Rab8 25. b3 $1 a5 26. Rc7 a4 27. bxa4 Ba8 28. a5 Rb7 29.
Rxc5 Ra7 30. Nc4 1-0

